def: One who confers a benefit or benefits. Bacon.
An ancient species of divination by means of plants, esp. sageand fig leaves.
A work having two parapets whose faces unite so as to form asalient angle toward the enemy.

An asexual zooid, usually forming one of a series of larvalforms in the agamic reproduction of various trematodes and otherparasitic worms. The sporocyst generally develops from an egg, but inits turn produces other larv√¶ by internal budding, or by thesubdivision of a part or all of its contents into a number of minutegerms. See Redia.
The title of the native sovereigns of Hyderabad, in India,since 1719.
Hoggish character or manners; selfishness; greed; beastliness.Crime and shame And all their hoggery. Mrs. Browning.
An argument retorted on an opponent. Milton.
To drive from a camp. [Obs.] Holland.
